{"questionId":"12880","questionHtml":"<p>Solve the inequality <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{x^2} > 2x + 1\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x <&nbsp; - 0.414,\\,\\,x > 2.41\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>0.414</mn>\n  <mo>,</mo>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mn>2.41</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {x < 1 - \\sqrt 2 ,\\,\\,x > 1 + \\sqrt 2 } \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>&lt;</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n      <mo>,</mo>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>&gt;</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em>&nbsp;for −0.414, 2.41 and <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for correct inequalities.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12880","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ1.H_8a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Solve the inequality x 2 > 2 x + 1 .","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Proof by induction, contradiction, counterexamples"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}